## Behavior

- Read the relevant repo's `AGENTS.md` or `CLAUDE.md` before making changes in any subdirectory.
- Use GSD commands (`/gsd-plan-phase`, `/gsd-execute-phase`, `/gsd-verify-work`, etc.) for structured work.
- Consult `.planning/codebase/` for pre-analyzed codebase intelligence before reasoning about architecture.
- Do not assume repos are one unified system — they are a portfolio. See `.planning/codebase/ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- Do not hand-edit `ade-repos.txt` or `{{ ade_name }}.code-workspace` — both are rendered from `.copier-answers.yml`. To refresh this ADE, run `uvx copier recopy --trust --skip-answered --overwrite`; to change the portfolio, drop `--skip-answered` and re-answer `portfolio_groups` / `extra_repos`.
{% if include_gsd_docs -%}
- `.planning/` is a symlink into `gsd-docs/`. Commit planning changes in `gsd-docs/` (push to `docs` branch), code changes per-repo.
{% endif -%}

## Terraform / OpenTofu

- Always run `terraform validate` and `terraform plan` before claiming a change is safe.
- In `parloa-infra-pre-stamp/`: never edit `*.tm.hcl` directly; use the generator scripts.
- Check the relevant module registry in `parloa-terraform-modules/` before writing inline resources.

## Kubernetes

- Argo CD is the deployment mechanism in `parloa-k8s/`.
- Stamp automation is one subsystem inside that repo, not the repo's whole purpose.
- Respect sync-wave annotations and GitOps ordering.
